<apex:page tabStyle="Sequence__c" showHeader="false" standardStylesheets="true">
    
    <style>
        body {background: url('{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, "/inPageClouds.png")}') top left no-repeat;}
        a {text-decoration:none;}
    </style>
    
    <apex:pageBlock mode="maindetail" title="Introducing Sequences">
        <apex:pageBlockSection columns="2" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p>A Sequence is an arrangement of multiple processing tasks called Steps.</p>
                <p>Each Sequence is known by a friendly name, for example 'ProcessInvoices', which should describe the nature of the work performed by its processing tasks or Steps.</p>
                <p>The EDA framework will advance Messages through the Steps of a Sequence in the order you arrange. A typical sequence will contain many steps. See diagram:</p>
                
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <apex:image width="480" value="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Sequence/sequenceSteps.png')}" />
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection title="When building a new Sequence" columns="1" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <ul>
                    <li>Any Steps after the Terminate Process will not be executed.</li>
                    <li>Each Step in the Sequence has an associated Process, a numbered Position, and potentially a Configuration.</li>
                    <li>It is the orchestrator's responsibility to ensure the Terminate Process is the final Step in every Sequence. This is provided for you and cannot be deleted.</li>
                </ul>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection title="Detail Page Buttons" columns="1" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Sequence/newStep.png')}" /> will append a new step (holding your chosen process) to the sequence. You can drag and drop to reposition each step.</p>
                <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Sequence/injectTestMessage.png')}" /> enqueues a message (carrying your user record) to this sequence. The message will progress through all the steps.</p>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection title="Tutorials :" columns="1" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <ul>
                    <li> Build a simple <a href="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/ConfirmSetupTutorial.html')}" style="color: #00f;">WireTap</a> sequence.
                    </li>
                    <li> Build a simple <a href="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/ScrapeWebPageTutorial.html')}" style="color: #00f;">Web Scrape</a> sequence.
                    </li>
                    <li> Build a sequence that groups messages under a <a href="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/LogUnderCommonIdentifierTutorial.html')}" style="color: #00f;">Common Identifier</a>.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>  
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection title="Click [Continue] to proceed." columns="1" collapsible="false" />
    </apex:pageBlock>
    
</apex:page>